<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1923-11-16T10:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1923-11-16T10:00:00-05:00" n="369" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d369">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">815.00/2753: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Honduras</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Morales</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Tegucigalpa</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1923-11-16T09:00:00-06:00"><hi rend="italic">November 16,
                                        1923—9 a.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received 8:35
                            p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>94. The President invited the three Presidential candidates to confer
                            with him yesterday afternoon. Carias refused to attend. The President,
                            Arias and Bonilla discussed the political situation for three hours but
                            nothing was accomplished.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Morales</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>